`git show` works with binary

___

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/427207/can-git-hook-scripts-be-managed-along-with-the-repository#37861972

I did this
`git config core.hooksPath hooks`

___

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5153199/git-show-content-of-file-as-it-will-look-like-after-committing/#5153379
Use the : prefix to access objects in the current index (staged but not yet commited).
`git show :file`
